JOB SUMMARY:
The incumbent will assemble sensor fittings products in the production line.

RESPONSIBILITIES:

  Assembly and testing of flow control products
  Adhere to quality procedures as required by company QMS quality manuals/procedures
  Work with cross-functional teams to meet customer’s expectations with speed, efficiency, and consistent quality.

REQUIREMENTS:

  NITEC/ITC, Technical certificate or equivalent in Mechanical, Electrical/Instrumentation Engineering
  Minimum 2 to 3 years of hands-on experience in assembly/repair of valves and/or actuators an advantage
  Physically fit, Hardworking with good integrity and a good team player
